AB  - Agaricoid basidiomycetes of the plain part of the Komi Republic are still not investigated enough. The research was started in 2011 and Syktyvkar city and its vicinity were selected as key areas (61°40'N, 50°49'E). The study area is located in the northeast of the European part of Russia in the middle taiga. 267 species and intraspecific taxa of the agaricoid basidiomycetes from 75 genera, 26 families and five orders were identified. 114 species are reported for Syktyvkar city and its vicinity for the first time, 73 species - for the Komi Republic for the first time. Four species (Phaeolepiota aurea, Cortinarius violaceus, Lepista nuda, Gyroporus cyanescens) are included in the Red Book of the Komi Republic. 218 species were found in forest habitats; mycorrhizal fungi, saprotrophic on wood and on litter prevailed among them. 53 species were registered in parks and lawns; saprotrophic on humus, on wood and mycorrhizal fungi prevailed among them. 17 species of agaricoid basidiomycetes mainly from the group of saprotrophic on humus were noted from meadows. An annotated list of identified species of agaricoid basidiomycetes growing in Syktyvkar and vicinity is given in this paper. {\textcopyright} 2017 Russian Academy of Sciences. All rights reserved.
